---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="About - TakeHomePay.nz New Zealand Salary Calculator" description="Learn about TakeHomePay.nz, the free New Zealand salary calculator built by Mottalib Radif. Understand how we calculate PAYE, KiwiSaver, and ACC levy.">
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://takehomepay.nz/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "About", "item": "https://takehomepay.nz/about/" }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-8">
    <nav class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-6">
      <a href="/" class="hover:text-primary">Home</a>
      <span class="mx-2">/</span>
      <span class="text-gray-800">About</span>
    </nav>

    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">About TakeHomePay.nz</h1>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Who Built This Calculator</h2>
      <div class="flex items-start gap-5 mb-4">
        <img src="/team/mottalib-radif.jpg" alt="Mottalib Radif" class="h-20 w-20 rounded-full object-cover border-4 border-white shadow-lg flex-shrink-0" width="80" height="80" loading="eager" />
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900">Mottalib Radif</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-primary font-medium">MBA, INSEAD &middot; NZ Personal Finance Enthusiast</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        TakeHomePay.nz was created by <strong>Mottalib Radif</strong>, an MBA graduate from INSEAD, one of the world's leading business schools. Passionate about New Zealand personal finance, Mottalib combines his expertise in financial technology with a deep understanding of the NZ tax system — PAYE brackets, KiwiSaver, ACC levy, and student loan repayments — to build accurate, transparent, and easy-to-use calculators. He has built salary calculators and financial planning applications for users across multiple countries, and is driven by the goal of making financial literacy tools freely available to everyone.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Our Mission</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        The mission of TakeHomePay.nz is to provide New Zealand employees, job seekers, and employers with a free, fast, and accurate salary calculator. Understanding your take-home pay in New Zealand involves navigating PAYE income tax brackets, KiwiSaver contributions, ACC earners' levy, and potentially student loan repayments. We aim to make this process simple and transparent so that every worker in New Zealand can quickly see exactly how much they will take home from their salary.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">How the Calculator Works</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Our calculator applies the current New Zealand PAYE income tax rates using the progressive tax brackets set by Inland Revenue (IRD). When you enter your gross salary, the tool calculates your PAYE tax, then deducts your chosen KiwiSaver employee contribution rate (3%, 4%, 6%, 8%, or 10%). It also calculates the ACC earners' levy based on the current rate and maximum liable earnings. If applicable, it includes student loan repayments at the standard repayment rate on income above the repayment threshold.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        The calculator shows your employer's KiwiSaver contribution and the total going into your KiwiSaver account. It produces a complete breakdown of your gross pay, each deduction, and your final net pay on an annual, monthly, fortnightly, and weekly basis. All calculations run entirely in your browser, ensuring your salary data remains private and is never sent to any external server.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Data Sources</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        All PAYE tax rates and thresholds are sourced from Inland Revenue New Zealand (ird.govt.nz). KiwiSaver contribution rates and employer contribution rules come from the KiwiSaver Act and IRD guidelines. ACC earners' levy rates are published by the Accident Compensation Corporation (acc.co.nz). Student loan repayment thresholds and rates are set by IRD and updated annually.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        This calculator is intended for estimation purposes only and does not replace professional tax advice. Your actual take-home pay may differ due to secondary income tax codes, specific tax credits like the Independent Earner Tax Credit, Working for Families entitlements, or other individual circumstances. We recommend checking with IRD or a qualified tax advisor for precise calculations based on your personal situation.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Contact</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        We welcome feedback, corrections, and feature suggestions from our users. If you notice any discrepancies with the current tax rates or have ideas for improving the calculator, please get in touch through our website. Your input helps us keep this tool accurate and useful for everyone in New Zealand.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>
